# ECCO · Netlify _redirects · place at root of etherealconnectionsco.com site
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Purpose: Decouple all client forms from the Google Apps Script deployment URL.
# Every client form points to `https://etherealconnectionsco.com/api/intake`
# (stable, brand-owned). This file proxies the request to the current GAS URL.
#
# When the GAS URL changes (Apps Script re-deploy creating a new URL, or GAS
# migration to a different script entirely), update ONLY the target URL below
# and redeploy this site. All downstream client forms keep working — no file
# edits, no other redeploys.
#
# The `200` status code is critical: it makes Netlify PROXY (not redirect).
# Browser sees same-origin request to etherealconnectionsco.com.
# A `301` or `302` would bounce the browser visibly to script.google.com.
#
# Syntax: <path>  <target URL>  <status>
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

/api/intake   https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycbx1CHUtI9XR-UPRvWUtUpjoye6yqiVObqCJXXu1OZL23Ortne8KzBWXuRO6ZT_MO-d3/exec   200
